    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/motoring-services-strategy"/>
    <title>Motoring services strategy</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This consultation seeks views on reforms which will put customers and businesses closer to the heart of the 4 motoring services agencies:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/dvla/"&gt;Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/driving-standards-agency"&gt;Driving Standards Agency&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/vca/"&gt;Vehicle Certification Agency&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/"&gt;Vehicle and Operator Services Agency&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;It outlines 6 major drivers which will accomplish this vision. These are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;maximising digital services&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;reforming the Vehicle Certification Agency to support economic growth and vehicle manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;bringing the driving test closer to the customer&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;transforming heavy goods vehicle, bus and coach testing&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;delivering better customer services through dialogue with our customers&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;defining our organisations to provide better services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
